First, the abrasion resistance of the coatings was tested according to the specifications of ISO 7784-2 using Taber Abraser equipment from Elcometer, and the observed results confirm that the prepared coatings have a good resistance to abrasion (Table 1
                     , Fig. 9
                     ). The experimental conditions were set at 500 cycles at a speed of 60 cycles/min, and the abrasive wheel used was CS-10, calibrated with a load of 500 g. This test was performed in duplicate on the control bare PU coating and one PU coating CQDs' concentration of 30 mg/gPU. Table 1 summarizes the average values and the respective standard deviations of the mass losses obtained for the test specimens. to investigate the impact of the CQDs being incorporated. Importantly, the obtained results evidence.
